The.Years.That.Made.Us.s01e01.The.Roaring.20s

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/10/26/42295794ed19420712d25e331b7a70bc.jpg[/img]

It's 1919 and Australia is reeling. Sixty thousand dead left in European soil and a nation tearing itself apart. Industrial violence, political extremism, 12% unemployment and a struggling rural economy are the backdrop for a new Federation fighting to survive. Into this maelstrom come three war heroes desperate for the peace they deserve.

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/10/26/2f2ccad9c562761f7b8df942eb7c6e51.png[/img]

The.Years.That.Made.Us.s01e02.Survival

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/10/31/5adf598987855910d93558546070d8e9.jpg[/img]

Chris Masters examines the events that laid the foundation for Australia in the 21st century. Episode 2 focuses on the Great Depression, which damaged Australia more deeply and longer than almost any other nation. Yet we survived.

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/10/31/e9e9d7114b053cc881a98ec79ae8efa6.png[/img]

The.Years.That.Made.Us.s01e03.Gathering.Storms

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/11/09/fbc4e5b3d2886ff1ea8c6c1f76bd2353.png[/img]

In a nation only just recovered from WWI and the Great Depression, the thought of another war was unthinkable. Yet as the 1930s unfold it becomes clear that the fragile Federation is under threat once more.

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/11/09/5bf72b5d8ca8fe6659f50e7fdfdcb0b8.jpg[/img]
